UML:TaggedValue.value: This class defines an interface for communicating with Colleague objects.
Each colleague class knows its mediator object and communicates with its mediator whenever it would have otherwise communicated with another colleague.
This class implements co-operative behaviour by co-ordinating Colleague objects. It also knows and maintains its colleagues.

This pattern defines an object that encapsulates how a set of objects interact. Mediator promotes loose coupling by keeping objects from referring to each other explicitly, and it lets you vary their interaction independently.
